This file summarizes changes made between Object Professional versions 1.22
and 1.30.  It is of interest primarily to users who have upgraded from
version 1.22.

Bugs fixed
---------------------------------------------------------------------------

OPDATE
  - Problems when picture characters were used in the DayString and
    MonthString arrays

OPDRAG
  - cpGetKey wasn't giving up timeslices in OS/2 and Windows DOS boxes

OPEDITOR
  - "Search again" not functional when block searching turned on

OPENHKBD
  - Alt key could stick under certain keyboard/BIOS combinations

OPFIELD
  - Garbage character sometimes displayed at the end of a simple
    string field.

OPFEDIT
  - CalcEditor broken by change in OPRO 1.21.  Would not allow you to enter
    a decimal point before entering a number.

OPFORM
  - Shaded fields not relative to current block
  - LJRule would use a bad pattern ID for drawing lines in some cases

OPMACED
  - Was referring directly to segment $0040

OPPICK
  - FlexWriting not handled properly in some rare cases
  - Span header redraws could overwrite highlight bar

OPSELECT/OPENTRY/OPDIALOG
  - Field visitation order incorrect around protected/hidden fields.

OPTSR
  - In rare cases, a program could crash if it EXECed another program
    after installing a popup routine.

OPTSR/OPSWAP
  - Was checking for DOS versions <= 5.99

PTIME
  - On-screen clock was not being updated properly
  - Crashes when clock displayed with a BP7 compile


New Features
---------------------------------------------------------------------------

OPCMD
  - Added a new user hook: "UserMatchFunc"

OPCTRL/OPDIALOG
  - Added support for the protection of individual cluster items

OPDATE
  - Routines added to convert between DOS dates and OPRO dates

OPDIR
  - Added methods to save and restore PathLists from disk

OPDOS
  - Add IsPhantom function to determine if a drive is a phantom drive
  - Various changes to protect against the selection/access of
    phantom drives

OPDRAG
  - Added CloseHotCode standard hot code

OPEDITOR
  - Added append block function
  - Added whole word searching

OPENTRY
  - EntryScreen now exits Process on ccAltKey commands

OPFIELD
  - Incrementing/decrementing a choice field now calls PostEdit routine
  - TextField and SelectField code and assorted constants moved to
    OPSELECT to facilitate PMode debugging

OPROOT
  - Added "Reset" method to SingleList and DoubleList

OPSTRING
  - Added Replace and ReplaceUC functions for flexible replacing

OPWINDOW
  - OPWINDOW split into OPWINDOW and OPABSWIN in order to allow PMode
    debugging

MAKEMENU
  - Better default identifiers generated for menu choices
